Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setSrouteMode(25.10)                                      setSrouteMode(25.10)

Name
       setSrouteMode - Comprises some of the sroute -extraConfig options

Syntax
       setSrouteMode

       [-help]

       [-allowWrongWayRoute {true | false}]

       [-avoidOverCoreRowLayer <layerName>]

       [-blockPinConnectRingPinCorners {true | false}]

       [-blockPinRouteWithPinWidth {true | false}]

       [-connectBrokenCorePin {true | false}]

       [-corePinIgnoreObs   {none   |   placement_blockage   |  overlap_obs  |
       block_halo}]

       [-corePinJoinLimit <value>]

       [-corePinLength <value>]

       [-corePinMaxViaScale <widthPct heightPct>]

       [-corePinSiteRailWidth {{<site1 layer11 Width11 layer12  Width12>  ...}
       {<site2 layer21 Width21 layer22 Width22> ...} ...}]

       [-corePinSnapTo {M1_pin | opt_routing_track | grid | half_grid}]

       [-corePinStopRoute {RowEnd | CellPinEnd}]

       [-corePinReferenceMacro {<macro1 macro2> ...}]

       [-corePinReferToFollowPin {true | false}]

       [-extendNearestTarget {true | false}]

       [-jogThresholdRatio <value>]

       [-layerNormalCost layer1 cost1 layer2 cost2 ...]

       [-layerWrongWayCost layer1 cost1 layer2 cost2 ...]

       [-padPinMinViaSize <viaSizePercent>]

       [-padRingLefConvention {true | false}]

       [-secondaryPinMaxGap <value>]

       [-secondaryPinRailWidth <value>]

       [-signalPinAsPG {true | false}]

       [-splitLongVia      {<threshold_value      step_value      offset_value
       height_value>}]

       [-targetNumber <value>]

       [-targetSearchDistance dist]

       [-timeLimit <value>]

       [-treatEndcapAsCore {true | false}]

       [-treatWelltapAsEndcap <cell_name_list>]

       [-viaConnectToShape {padring | ring | stripe | blockring |  blockpin  |
       coverpin | noshape | blockwire | corewire | followpin | iowire}]

       [-viaThruToClosestRing {true | false}]

       [-corePinLengthAsInstance {true | false}]

       [-padPinSplit  {<width  spacing>  |  <width1  spacing1  width2 spacing2
       width3 spacing3 ...>}]

       [-srpgAonCellPin {cellName:pinName}]

       [-reset]

       Comprises some of the sroute -extraConfig options. It is recommended to
       use setSrouteMode for sroute.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each setSrouteMode parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setSrouteMode

       -allowWrongWayRoute {true | false}
              Allow wrong way routing.

              Default: false

              Note: If the metal1 preferred routing direction is vertical  and
              standard  cells  have  their  VDD  and VSS pins on layer metal1,
              sroute will route metal1 wires on horizontal direction  to  con-
              tinue  extending the followpin connections to core rings by this
              option.

       -avoidOverCoreRowLayer <layerName>
              Specifies the number of layers to avoid routing of block pin and
              pad pin over the core row area.

              Default: max layer of standard cell pin

       -blockPinConnectRingPinCorners {true|false}
              Specifies whether to extend the ring pins at corners.

              Default: false

       -blockPinRouteWithPinWidth {true|false}
              Specifies that the block wire used for a connection is  to  have
              the same width as the pin from which it connects.

              Default: false

       -corePinJoinLimit <value>
              Joins  follow  pin  rail gaps smaller than this variable, bigger
              gaps will remain open. The option is of type float.

              Default: 0

       -corePinLength <value>
              Connects core pins of specified length. The option  is  of  type
              float.

              Default: 0

       -corePinLengthAsInstance {true | false}
              Connects  core  pins  whose length equals or is greater than the
              length of instance.

              Default: false

       -corePinMaxViaScale <widthPct heightPct>
              Controls the length and width of vias at the crossover  of  core
              pin  rails and stripes. Specify this value as percentages of the
              width of the via at the top of the  stack.  Smaller  vias  leave
              room for more routing tracks on layers between the vias.

              Default: If you do not specify this parameter, the software uses
              a value of 100, which specifies a full-size via.

       -connectBrokenCorePin {true | false}
              When  set  to  true,  sroute checks the signal pin, second power
              pin, and obs, and then breaks the followpin to avoid violations.
              When set to false, sroute does not check internal geometries and
              does not break the followpin.

              Note that for ABUTMENT standardcell  pins,  followpins  will  go
              through  the  pin;  for  FEEDTHRU standard cell pins, followpins
              will break at the at the pin edge on the standard cell boundary.
              Refer to LEF/DEF Language Reference for more details.

              See the examples below for understanding the usage of this para-
              meter:

              For ABUTMENT Standard Cell Pins:

              setSrouteMode -connectBrokenCorePin false

              setSrouteMode -connectBrokenCorePin true

              For FEEDTHRU Standard Cell Pins:

              setSrouteMode -connectBrokenCorePin false

              setSrouteMode -connectBrokenCorePin true

              Default: false

       -corePinIgnoreObs {none | placement_blockage | overlap_obs |
       block_halo}
              Ignores the specified blockage while connecting the follow pin.

       -corePinReferenceMacro {<macro1 macro2> ...}
              Uses specified standard cell master's cell  name  as  references
              for followpin creation. If you specify multiple macros for a row
              height,  the  software  picks the first macro as reference. This
              parameter is of <string >type.

              Default: ""

       -corePinSiteRailWidth {{<site1 layer11 Width11 layer12 Width12> ...}
       {<site2 layer21 Width21 layer22 Width22> ...} ...}
              Defines the followpin layer width for the  specified  site  rail
              for  followpin  generation.  The followpin width defined by this
              parameter has higher priority than the width of the  same  layer
              defined  in  the  macro  LEF, but lower than that defined by the
              sroute -corePinWidth parameter.

              Following are the values used with this parameter:

              * site: Specifies the site name defined in the LEF file.

              * layer: Specifies the name of the  layer  defined  in  the  LEF
                file.

              * width:  Specifies  the  followpin  width on the top and bottom
                sides of the defined site.

       -corePinSnapTo {M1_pin | opt_routing_track | grid | half_grid}
              Snaps metal2 followpins in the location to save  routing  tracks
              in a preventive manner. When set to:

              * M1_pin: Generated metal2 followpins are snapped to metal1 std-
                cell pin center.

              * opt_routing_track:  Generated metal2 followpins are snapped to
                track or half track to save routing tracks.

              * grid: Generated metal2 followpins are snapped to  the  nearest
                routing track.

              * half_grid:  Generated  metal2  followpins  are  snapped to the
                nearest half routing track.

              Default: M1_pin

              Note: This option can only work when the option -corePinReferTo-
              FollowPin is set to true.

       -corePinStopRoute {RowEnd | CellPinEnd}
              Allows the command to extend the follow pin wire. Following  are
              the parameter values:

              * RowEnd: Extends the follow pin wire to the row-end.

              * CellPinEnd: Extends the follow pin wire to the cell-end.

              Default: RowEnd

       -corePinReferToFollowPin {true | false}
              If  set  to true, sroute generates followpins based on the stan-
              dard followpins, whether or not there are standard cell pins  on
              the  defined  metal layer. Standard followpins refer to the fol-
              lowpins on the first routing layer. This parameter can  be  used
              with any set of layers with same direction. Following is a usage
              example of this parameter:

              setSrouteMode -corePinReferToFollowPin 1 ...

              sroute -corePinLayer M2 -corePinWidth w1 ... #w0 is the standard
              followpin's width

              Following is the output of the above command:

              Default: false

       -extendNearestTarget {true | false}
              Extends  the nearest target so that it can be connected. The op-
              tion is of type bool.

              Default: false

       -jogThresholdRatio <value>
              Defines the distance  ratio  between  a  jogging  target  and  a
              straight target. The option is of type float.

              Default: 10

       -layerNormalCost<layer1 cost1 layer2 cost2 ...>
              Specifies  layer  cost  of preferred direction. The option is of
              type: string.

              Default: ""

       -layerWrongWayCost <layer1 cost1 layer2 cost2  ...>
              Specifies layer cost of non-preferred direction.

              Default: ""

       -padPinMinViaSize viaSizePercent
              Permits the software to reduce the size of vias at pad pins when
              changing layers, if there is not enough room for a standard size
              via.

              Default: If you do not specify this parameter, the software uses
              a value of 20, which permits vias that are 20% of  the  standard
              via size.

       -padPinSplit {<width spacing> | <width1 spacing1 width2 spacing2 width3
       spacing3 ...>}
              Splits the width and spacing to connect wide pad pins.

              When you use {<width spacing>}, sroute repeats it to connect the
              wide pad pins. It stops when the rest distance cannot put a full
              width  wire.  When  you  use  {<width1  spacing1 width2 spacing2
              width3 spacing3 ...>}, sroute sets the connection for  wide  pad
              pins  only  once.  It  stops when the rest distance cannot put a
              full width wire.

              Refer to the command usage in various  cases  and  corresponding
              outputs below:

              setSrouteMode -padPinSplit {width spacing}

              setSrouteMode -padPinSplit {W1 S1 W2 S2 W3 S3}

              setSrouteMode -padPinSplit {W1 S1 W2 S2 W3 S3 W4 S4 W5 S5 W6 S6}

              Default: ""

       -padRingLefConvention {true | false}
              Routes  the  pad rings based on the information specified in the
              LEF file. If set to 0, Innovus chooses the  pad  pin  connection
              style  (ABUTMENT or FEEDTHRU) when routing pad rings, disregard-
              ing what is specified in the LEF file. The  option  is  of  type
              Boolean.

              Default: true

       -reset Resets  all  or  specified  options to default value. Any values
              that do not already match the default value and are reset.  will
              be reported.

       -secondaryPinMaxGap <value>
              Specifies  variable  value for gaps bigger than this value cause
              level shifter rail to break. The option type is float.

              Default: 0

       -secondaryPinRailWidth <value>
              Specifies width of followpin rail. The option type is float.

              Default: 0

       -signalPinAsPG {true | false}
              Specifies signal pins as PG pins in pad ring creation. When this
              parameter is set to true, the sroute  -nets  parameter  supports
              wildcard characters (like * and ?).

              Default: false

       -splitLongVia {<threshold_value step_value offset_value height_value>}
              Splits  vias  longer than the specified length (threshold_value,
              in micrometers) into smaller vias with specified  center-to-cen-
              ter spacing (step_value, in micrometers), left/bottom end offset
              (offset_value,  in  micrometers)  and vertical/horizontal height
              (height_value, in micrometers) values . This is  independent  of
              the option -split_via.

              Default: If you do not specify this parameter, the software does
              not split vias.

              Note: If the offset_value is given as negative, the vias will be
              placed  symmetrically  on  both  ends. The default value of off-
              set_value is -1.

       -srpgAonCellPin {<cellName: pinName>}
              Lists the cell/pin information NOT extracted from CPF.

              Default: ""

       -targetNumber <value>
              Specify number of target to connect. The option type is int.

              Default: 0 (minimum). Maximum is 100000.

       -targetSearchDistance <dist>
              Specifies target search distance. The option type is float.

              Default: 0

       -timeLimit <value>
              Specify time limit (in seconds) that the router  is  allowed  in
              routing each port. The option type is float.

              Default: 0

       -treatEndcapAsCore {true | false}
              Specifies  to  treat Endcap macro as core macro. The option type
              is bool.

              Default: false

       -treatWelltapAsEndcap <cell_name_list>
              Enables sroute to treat the Welltap cells as the  Endcap  cells.
              Additionally,  the  ENDCAP  class  cells are ignored by default,
              when generating the followpin wires.

              Default: ""

       -viaConnectToShape {padring | ring | stripe | blockring | blockpin |
       coverpin | noshape | blockwire | corewire | followpin | iowire}
              Specifies which shapes vias can connect to.

              The option type is enum.

               Default:  padring  ring  stripe  blockring  blockpin   coverpin
              noshape blockwire corewire followpin iowire

       -viaThruToClosestRing {true | false}
              Specifies  that  a  via  should connect only to the closest ring
              layer when multiple rings overlap.

              Default: If you do not specify this parameter, vias  connect  to
              all overlapping rings.

Examples
       The following command defines followpin layer width for generating fol-
       lowpins:

       setSrouteMode  -corePinSiteRailWidth  {{site1  layer1 w1} {site2 layer1
       w2}}

